definitions.definition: ( countable ) A hit or strike with one's fist .
( countable , rare ) A blow from something other than the fist.

examples: The tornado is finally losing its punch .

main_definition: ( countable ) A hit or strike with one's fist .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , rare ) A blow from something other than the fist.

definitions.definition: ( countable ) A device, generally slender and round, used for creating holes in thin material, for driving an object through a hole in a containing object, or to stamp or emboss a mark or design on a surface.

subdefinitions.definition: ( countable ) A mechanism for punching holes in paper or other thin material .

definitions.definition: ( countable ) A hole or opening created with a punch.
( piledriving ) An extension piece applied to the top of a pile ; a dolly .
A prop , as for the roof of a mine .

definitions.definition: A beverage , generally containing a mixture of fruit juice and some other beverage, often alcoholic.

definitions.definition: Any of various riodinid butterflies of the genus Dodona of Asia.
